pr_body:
Hi all,
Here is a PR for sampling correlation matrices with uniform billiard walk.
Main new files are:
* ./examples/correlation_matrices/ (user functions for sampling, test functions)
* ./include/convex_bodies/correlation_matrices/ (new correlation matrix class)
* ./include/matrix_operations/EigenvaluesCorrelation.h (modified eigenvalue problems)

To test: execute bash script ./examples/correlation_matrices/test.sh then input a value for n from keyboard.
The code will run the new implementation and the one use Spectrahedron class and their timings. There is a commented line
check_output in test.hpp which can be uncommented to check the correctness of output,

The speed up comes from reflection operator (adapt the computation with special LMI) and linear intersection (Eigen Generalized Self Adjoint Solver is faster than Spectra SymGEigSolver (tested up to n = 18)).

But originally, the "uniform" random point generator does not have const keyword for Polytope parameters. This allows the call of BilliardWalk on Spectrahedron. Adding const in Gaussian RPG will prevent using random walks which change precomputedValues (e.g. through line_positive_intersect) with Spectrahedron, including my ReHMC Walk in the second PR. But I will leave that problem for later.

Logically, having const there is reasonable and maybe the current implementation of Spectrahedron is the one making troubles. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 9, 7, 22, 2, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'huuphuocle', 'type': 'User'}]

Hi all,
Here is a PR for reviewing my implementation of ReHMC Walk for Gaussian and Exponential truncated distribution for the two classes CorreSpectra and CorreSpectra_MT from my first PR https://github.com/GeomScale/volesti/pull/233.
